title: Collected Poems of Rupert Brooke
creator: Rupert Brooke
description: LibriVox recording of "Collected Poems of Rupert Brooke", read by Graham Redman Rupert Chawner Brooke (August 3, 1887 – April 23, 1915) was an English poet known for his idealistic War Sonnets written during the First World War (especially The Soldier), as well as for his poetry written outside of war, especially The Old Vicarage, Grantchester and The Great Lover. He was also known for his boyish good looks, which prompted the Irish poet William Butler Yeats to describe him as "the handsomest young man in England". (Summary from Wikipedia) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B format available
